.TH runit-halt 8
.SH NAME
runit-halt \- stop the system
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B init
0
.br
.B runit-halt
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B runit-halt
causes the Unix process no 1
.BR runit (8)
to halt the system. Normally
.B runit-halt
is run by
.BR runit-init (8)
if called as
.B init 0\fR.
.P
To signal
.BR runit (8)
the system halt request,
.B runit-halt
removes the /etc/runit/reboot file and touches /etc/runit/stopit. Then a CONT
signal is sent to
.BR runit (8).
.SH EXIT CODES
.B runit-halt
always returns 0.
.SH SEE ALSO
runit-init(8),
runit(8),
runit-reboot(8)
